Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a machine learning approach using a Deep Graph Convolutional Neural Network (DGCNN) model to predict the feasibility of solutions obtained during the run of the LS heuristic. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
2. cs.LG - The paper uses a machine learning approach to improve the efficiency of the LS heuristic. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
3. cs.RO - The paper deals with the Train Unit Shunting Problem (TUSP), which is a scheduling and routing problem. This falls under the domain of robotics and control.
4. cs.DS - The paper uses a machine learning approach to improve the efficiency of the LS heuristic. This involves handling and processing large amounts of data, which falls under the domain of data science.
5. cs.SY - The paper deals with the Train Unit Shunting Problem (TUSP), which is a scheduling and routing problem. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
